- You're my number one, Dad.

23:18.467 --> 23:20.400
- [laughs]

23:20.400 --> 23:21.700
- Are the people nice
you're working with?

23:21.700 --> 23:23.734
- So far, it's hard

23:23.734 --> 23:26.667
to, like, walk
onto a new boat, new crew.

23:26.667 --> 23:28.200
I'm feeling really alone.

23:28.200 --> 23:29.600
Um...
- Yeah.

23:29.600 --> 23:31.667
- Yeah.

23:31.667 --> 23:33.567
My parents have been
going through an ugly divorce

23:33.567 --> 23:35.367
for a couple years now,

23:35.367 --> 23:38.233
and I came to Croatia
to escape that.

23:38.233 --> 23:40.767
I love them both, but I don't
want to be caught in the middle.

23:40.767 --> 23:42.367
Now, like, I'm replacing
my mom and dad

23:42.367 --> 23:44.367
with, like, Bobby and Hannah.

23:44.367 --> 23:46.500
- You have a lot of experience,
like, meeting new people,

23:46.500 --> 23:48.700
so it shouldn't be
that much of a challenge.

23:48.700 --> 23:52.767
- It's been a challenge,
but I can get through it.

23:52.767 --> 23:54.633
Talking to my dad always helps.

23:54.633 --> 23:56.767
I feel that I need
to focus on my job

23:56.767 --> 23:59.100
and continue to do my job
the best I can.

23:59.100 --> 24:00.700
- Time for me
to say good night.

24:00.700 --> 24:02.500
- All right, I love you.

24:02.500 --> 24:04.467
- Love you too, sweetheart.

24:04.467 --> 24:09.033
[energetic music]

24:09.033 --> 24:10.567
- Gorgeous night
to go to bed early.

24:10.567 --> 24:12.367
- Perfect.
Good night, guys.

24:12.367 --> 24:13.467
- Bye, everybody.

24:13.467 --> 24:20.667
♪ ♪

24:20.667 --> 24:23.767
- I thought we were gonna be
nice and comfortable up here.

24:23.767 --> 24:26.500
Honey, I just have to say,
like,

24:26.500 --> 24:28.667
honestly,
I've blown away by you.

24:28.667 --> 24:30.533
I'm very much surprised as--

24:30.533 --> 24:32.767
- To be honest, I've actually
surprised myself.

24:32.767 --> 24:34.467
It's good to be, like,
out on the floor

24:34.467 --> 24:36.533
and have people around
and, you know,

24:36.533 --> 24:38.367
your mind's just,
like, distracted.

24:38.367 --> 24:39.533
- Yeah.

24:42.734 --> 24:45.667
- What my mom must be
dealing with knowing that

24:45.667 --> 24:48.333
she's not gonna see her
drive up our driveway every day

24:48.333 --> 24:51.100
or, you know, go and have
a coffee with her...

24:53.400 --> 24:55.100
That's the hard part, is--

24:59.300 --> 25:00.633
- You lost your brother?
- Mm.

25:01.567 --> 25:02.633
- Mm.

25:04.367 --> 25:06.300
I was really young
when my brother got sick,

25:06.300 --> 25:08.300
and he passed away
very quickly.

25:08.300 --> 25:10.033
When something
like that happens,

25:10.033 --> 25:12.400
the innocence of your
childhood, I guess,

25:12.400 --> 25:13.667
is taken away a little bit.

25:13.667 --> 25:15.367
- Was he younger
or older than you?

25:16.367 --> 25:17.400
- Wow.
- Yeah.

25:25.000 --> 25:26.700
- Since then, I really feel like

25:26.700 --> 25:29.700
I've been living every day
like it's my last.

25:29.700 --> 25:32.700
So every opportunity I have,
I take it with both hands.

25:36.433 --> 25:39.300
- Yeah, thank you.

25:39.300 --> 25:41.467
- And for now, you have me.

25:41.467 --> 25:42.700
- Thank you.

25:42.700 --> 25:47.066
[beeping]

25:47.066 --> 25:49.033
[beeping stops]

25:49.033 --> 25:52.333
[upbeat music]

25:52.333 --> 25:54.467
♪ ♪

25:54.467 --> 25:57.333
- Good morning.
- Another day in paradise.

25:57.333 --> 25:59.066
To be honest,
I am not feeling much better

25:59.066 --> 26:00.400
than I was yesterday.

26:00.400 --> 26:02.166
It's time to squeeze oranges.

26:02.166 --> 26:08.533
♪ ♪

26:08.533 --> 26:10.066
- Is it gonna be
one of those days today?

26:10.066 --> 26:11.667
- Oh, yeah.
- Oh, Malia,

26:11.667 --> 26:14.066
you're not a morning person.
- No.

26:14.066 --> 26:17.066
I was up until 3:00
in the morning.

26:17.066 --> 26:18.533
I'm exhausted.

26:18.533 --> 26:19.734
I'm so excited that we get

26:19.734 --> 26:21.600
to pull up the anchors.

26:21.600 --> 26:23.367
Charter guests
are getting off today.

26:23.367 --> 26:25.100
And, boom. Easy.

26:25.100 --> 26:26.734
- How are you this morning?

26:26.734 --> 26:29.367
- Great. How are you?
- Very well, thank you.

26:29.367 --> 26:30.633
- It's wonderful.

26:30.633 --> 26:34.367
♪ ♪

26:34.367 --> 26:35.767
- Good morning.

26:35.767 --> 26:37.734
The table looks beautiful.
- Yeah?

26:37.734 --> 26:39.734
women: Morning.
- Andrea's here.

26:39.734 --> 26:41.367
- Last day.
- Yeah.

26:41.367 --> 26:42.700
- This is so nice.

26:42.700 --> 26:44.100
- All right, I pop this up.

26:44.100 --> 26:45.633
- So you're on.
- Low speed.

26:45.633 --> 26:46.700
- You can go high speed
for bringing it in.

26:46.700 --> 26:48.367
- Okay.

26:48.367 --> 26:49.600
- Okay, you can start
pulling up.

26:49.600 --> 26:51.166
- Okay.
Pulling anchor up.

26:51.166 --> 26:52.734
[heavy clattering]

26:52.734 --> 26:55.767
- Looks like we spun around
last night.

26:55.767 --> 26:58.767
[heavy clattering]

26:58.767 --> 27:01.767
[metallic clanging]

27:06.467 --> 27:08.400
[loud clang]
- What was that?

27:08.400 --> 27:09.667
- You all right?
- It won't come in any more.

27:09.667 --> 27:11.066
- Can you see the line?
- Mm-hmm.

27:11.066 --> 27:12.667
- Is it tight?
- Yeah.

27:12.667 --> 27:14.500
There's, like, a kink in it.
- Hey, um...

27:14.500 --> 27:15.633
why did you guys stop pulling
the anchor up?

27:15.633 --> 27:17.400
What's up?
- Captain,

27:17.400 --> 27:19.000
it's no longer coming up.
There might be a kink

27:19.000 --> 27:20.533
in the anchor chain.

27:20.533 --> 27:22.133
- Or it's twisted
on the other one.

27:22.133 --> 27:24.100
- Looks like port's
wrapped in itself,

27:24.100 --> 27:26.734
so I think we need to go out
on the tender to set it off.

27:28.533 --> 27:30.000
- How's this a way
to start a day?

27:32.467 --> 27:34.000
- Hey, Maxie, can you get
the key for the tender?

27:34.000 --> 27:35.066
- Where is it?
- Inside.

27:35.066 --> 27:36.667
It's the long white one.

27:36.667 --> 27:38.533
- We should start moving soon,
I would think.

27:38.533 --> 27:41.533
She said it was about
2 1/2 hours to get back.

27:41.533 --> 27:42.667
- All righty.
We're good to go.

27:42.667 --> 27:45.000
- Oh, f--- off, anchors.

27:45.000 --> 27:46.567
This sucks.

27:46.567 --> 27:48.533
Like, of course
this happens to me.

27:48.533 --> 27:51.033
First time pulling up
the anchor, like, of course.

27:51.033 --> 27:53.433
- Oh, sh--.
Look at that, bro.

27:53.433 --> 27:55.166
- Awesome. I hope
I don't get blamed for this one.

27:55.166 --> 27:57.266
- Is it wrapped--
- It's all, like, up

27:57.266 --> 27:59.100
and it's underneath the bow
all in one big group.

28:07.433 --> 28:08.567
I've never seen this before.

28:08.567 --> 28:10.166
This is really twisted.

28:10.166 --> 28:11.700
I'm looking at myself now
and just thinking,

28:11.700 --> 28:13.500
"I don't have
an actual solution to this."

28:13.500 --> 28:14.533
- Holy sh--.

28:22.633 --> 28:23.266
I've never seen this before.

28:24.700 --> 28:26.533
This is really twisted.

28:26.533 --> 28:28.133
I don't have
an actual solution to this.

28:28.133 --> 28:30.033
- Holy sh--.
- I wish we had something decent

28:30.033 --> 28:31.600
we could use to pull this with.
- Oh, my gosh.

28:31.600 --> 28:33.600
I just checked the time.
It's so late.

28:33.600 --> 28:35.700
both: Yeah.
- We haven't even left.

28:35.700 --> 28:37.600
- Okay, so let's get a line
tied on to chain.

28:37.600 --> 28:39.166
- The anchor chain
that's wrapped,

28:39.166 --> 28:40.300
around the port anchor,
is that correct?

28:40.300 --> 28:42.066
- Yeah, and we're gonna take

28:42.066 --> 28:43.200
the tension off of it
with the windlass.

28:43.200 --> 28:44.700
We're in big trouble right now

28:44.700 --> 28:46.567
because there's still
guests on board,

28:46.567 --> 28:48.600
and we need to get 'em
back to port ASAP.

28:48.600 --> 28:51.533
I have 60 meters of chain times
two hanging in the water.

28:51.533 --> 28:52.734
We can't drive the yacht
like this.

28:52.734 --> 28:54.200
Someone wake Bobby up.

28:54.200 --> 28:55.667
- Copy, Sandy.
I'll get him up.

28:55.667 --> 28:58.000
Bobby!
[knock at door]

28:58.000 --> 29:01.667
- This is a f---ing dump show.

29:01.667 --> 29:03.066
- Ready?
She's gonna pull it in a little.

29:03.066 --> 29:05.000
Go ahead.

29:05.000 --> 29:07.133
Pull it up.

29:07.133 --> 29:08.500
All right, that's good.

29:08.500 --> 29:09.500
That's good.
That's good.

29:09.500 --> 29:11.100
- Holy sh--.

29:11.100 --> 29:13.100
- The anchor being tangled
is exactly like

29:13.100 --> 29:14.767
a necklace that's tangled.

29:14.767 --> 29:16.233
It's the same thing.
You work the chain

29:16.233 --> 29:19.233
until it frees itself.

29:19.233 --> 29:21.600
- [laughs]
- [murmurs indistinctly]

29:21.600 --> 29:24.166
- I figured I'd come out here.
- Take a look.

29:24.166 --> 29:26.600
- Max, can you turn
that small line there?

29:26.600 --> 29:28.500
- What the hell?

29:28.500 --> 29:30.633
- Good morning, Bobby.
- What is that rat's nest?

29:30.633 --> 29:33.333
- Okay, now wrap that around,
and I'll tell you when to pull.

29:33.333 --> 29:34.567
Go ahead.

29:34.567 --> 29:36.233
- Okay, pulling up.

29:36.233 --> 29:38.600
- Sandy, I wouldn't
put your head in there.

29:38.600 --> 29:41.600
- No.
- Oop.

29:41.600 --> 29:43.233
- Oh, you have some things
in here.

29:43.233 --> 29:45.500
- Uh, what?
- Your bathing suit.

29:45.500 --> 29:48.033
[upbeat music]

29:48.033 --> 29:49.500
[laughter]

29:49.500 --> 29:51.000
- [whispers]
What is going on?

29:51.000 --> 29:52.734
- Anchor problems.
- Per usual.

29:52.734 --> 29:55.367
We are still in the same spot.
- That's insane.

29:55.367 --> 29:57.633
- Good thing we have all those
anchor watches.

29:57.633 --> 29:59.700
- It's just annoying 'cause
it delays guest departure.

30:01.133 --> 30:03.200
[creaking]

30:03.200 --> 30:05.133
[indistinct chatter]
- Oh! Stop, stop.

30:05.133 --> 30:07.133
- The poor guests, you know,

30:07.133 --> 30:09.000
they're sort of sticking their
heads over, having a look,

30:09.000 --> 30:11.233
and you're like,
"Oh, I don't want to say

30:11.233 --> 30:13.266
"that we're absolutely
up Sh-- Creek,

30:13.266 --> 30:15.533
but we're up Sh-- Creek
basically."

30:15.533 --> 30:16.667
F---ing hell.

30:16.667 --> 30:18.266
- You can loosen that line.

30:18.266 --> 30:19.734
Just don't let it go.

30:19.734 --> 30:21.400
- It's no joke
what they're working on.

30:21.400 --> 30:25.266
They're all manually trying
to untangle the chains.

30:25.266 --> 30:27.066
- Tighten up on your line,
Bobby.

30:27.066 --> 30:29.633
- Oh.
Stop on the starboard.

30:29.633 --> 30:31.166
- Let it go. Let it go.

30:31.166 --> 30:33.266
- I can't hold an anchor
with my hands.

30:33.266 --> 30:34.300
- No, the windlass.

30:34.300 --> 30:36.000
[mechanical creaking]

30:36.000 --> 30:37.033
- Coronas.

30:37.033 --> 30:38.133
- Yay!

30:38.133 --> 30:40.033
- Loosen the thinner line.

30:40.033 --> 30:42.033
But keep the line in your hand.
- Whoa, watch out.

30:42.033 --> 30:43.300
- Don't grab that
with your hand.

30:43.300 --> 30:45.166
- Yeah.
Dude. All right.

30:45.166 --> 30:46.667
I want Malia back.

30:46.667 --> 30:48.233
- Okay, I'll just walk away
then.

30:48.233 --> 30:50.300
- Yeah. Yeah.
- [laughs]

30:50.300 --> 30:53.133
- Got your head where there's
thousands of pounds of tension.

30:53.133 --> 30:55.233
- No, there isn't.
You don't know what's going on.

30:55.233 --> 30:57.166
Bobby's energy is not helpful.

30:57.166 --> 30:59.667
I need assistance,
not resistance.

30:59.667 --> 31:02.033
Can you get in the tender
with them?

31:02.033 --> 31:05.433
'Cause I think maybe
your strength could help.

31:05.433 --> 31:07.300
- Hey, you guys want
to pick me up over here?

31:07.300 --> 31:10.033
[groans]

31:10.033 --> 31:12.166
- I got some fresh smoothies
here.

31:12.166 --> 31:14.300
Can I offer anyone--
- I'll have a smoothie.

31:14.300 --> 31:16.266
- I think it's really important
for stewardesses

31:16.266 --> 31:19.467
that we keep the drama
to ourselves as crew

31:19.467 --> 31:22.066
and not let the guests
in on anything.

31:22.066 --> 31:25.200
Anyone with a cold beverage
is gonna be distracted and happy

31:25.200 --> 31:27.734
for a good couple of hours,
I would say.

31:27.734 --> 31:29.266
- Okay, so you got this one
around the top,

31:29.266 --> 31:30.734
which is back here,
which goes--

31:30.734 --> 31:32.133
- If I pull up on that
with the line,

31:32.133 --> 31:33.734
will it pull up the anchor?

31:33.734 --> 31:36.066
- You want to pull the anchor
with this line?

31:36.066 --> 31:37.433
- Yeah.
- That will not happen.

31:37.433 --> 31:39.200
- We just need
to pull the chain.

31:39.200 --> 31:44.066
- This has a strength
of maybe 1,000 pounds.

31:44.066 --> 31:45.467
- Tie it on and give me
the line,

31:45.467 --> 31:48.333
and then you can just stand back
if you're afraid.

31:48.333 --> 31:50.033
- Afraid.
- However,

31:50.033 --> 31:52.667
I've been doing this
for 27 years.

31:52.667 --> 31:55.767
I said you can stand back
while I pull up on the chain.

31:55.767 --> 31:57.233
Everyone's under
a lot of stress.

31:57.233 --> 31:58.333
Just take a breath.

32:00.100 --> 32:01.467
- You just gotta let her
talk through it.

32:01.467 --> 32:03.200
- But she wants
to call me scared?

32:03.200 --> 32:05.166
"Oh, if you're scared,
you can leave."

32:10.100 --> 32:11.367
All right, the line's going up.

32:11.367 --> 32:13.467
Stop there.
We got slack.

32:13.467 --> 32:15.233
- We're gonna go upstairs.

32:15.233 --> 32:17.100
I'm gonna try another
beautiful shot.

32:17.100 --> 32:18.333
- What are you gonna wear?

32:18.333 --> 32:19.367
- I'm totally naked.
- Okay.

32:22.100 --> 32:24.233
- Yeah, it's so sad.

32:24.233 --> 32:25.700
- Okay, stop.

32:25.700 --> 32:27.734
Greasy... [indistinct]
going port side.

32:27.734 --> 32:30.433
- So the chain that is
wrapped around the anchor,

32:30.433 --> 32:33.100
I want to drop that first,
that's in the water.

32:33.100 --> 32:35.367
We need to be able to pull
the bottom of that chain

32:35.367 --> 32:37.533
from underneath the anchor.

32:37.533 --> 32:38.533
- Let up a little bit.

32:38.533 --> 32:41.400
That top one.

32:41.400 --> 32:43.367
- The hard part is seeing

32:43.367 --> 32:45.467
what is actually going on
under there.

32:45.467 --> 32:47.333
- Where's his mask
and board shorts?

32:47.333 --> 32:48.533
He has get in the water.

32:48.533 --> 32:50.200
- If I do not get this undone,

32:50.200 --> 32:52.266
we're gonna have
to cut the anchor,

32:52.266 --> 32:54.000
and that's the last thing
you want to do on any boat,

32:54.000 --> 32:55.266
because it's
your emergency stop;

32:55.266 --> 32:56.400
it's your brake
in case something

32:56.400 --> 32:59.100
does go wrong with the engine.

33:01.500 --> 33:04.734
- Hey, everyone, I'm Kat Curtis
on a boat in Croatia,

33:04.734 --> 33:08.367
and you're watching Naked News.

33:08.367 --> 33:09.400
- Keep tensioning.

33:09.400 --> 33:11.100
- Huh?

33:11.100 --> 33:12.400
- Keep tensioning,
see what happens.

33:12.400 --> 33:14.100
[chains creaking]

33:14.100 --> 33:16.367
Yeah.
- All right, I'm gonna come.

33:16.367 --> 33:18.233
Come get me, Bobby.
- All right.

33:18.233 --> 33:19.767
- Hannah, Hannah.
Sandy.

33:19.767 --> 33:22.400
Could you please
call a water taxi?

33:22.400 --> 33:24.300
- Copy, Captain.
Will do.

33:24.300 --> 33:25.433
- Hi there.
It's Hannah calling

33:25.433 --> 33:27.367
from motor yacht "Sirocco."

33:27.367 --> 33:31.033
Would it be possible
to get a taxi service out here?

33:31.033 --> 33:33.166
Uh, like,
as soon as humanly possible?

33:33.166 --> 33:35.433
They were supposed to be off
at 12:00.

33:35.433 --> 33:38.033
- Wes.
Is there a place that looks

33:38.033 --> 33:40.333
like that we could tie
a rope on?

33:46.133 --> 33:48.400
- I am scared sh--less,

33:48.400 --> 33:51.533
'cause the last person
I want to see hurt is Wes.

33:51.533 --> 33:53.233
- These anchors weigh
a couple tons.

33:53.233 --> 33:55.033
And by pulling or pushing
the wrong way,

33:55.033 --> 33:57.033
they can unravel,
and you could potentially die.

33:57.033 --> 33:59.166
- No, no, no.
Wes, Wes, Wes.

33:59.166 --> 34:01.300
- But I'm so out of ideas,
I'm just trying to see

34:01.300 --> 34:03.233
from a safe distance
what I can do.

34:07.400 --> 34:07.533
- Okay.

34:09.200 --> 34:12.000
[clanking]

34:12.000 --> 34:13.133
Okay, that's good.

34:13.133 --> 34:14.333
- Sh--.

34:14.333 --> 34:15.734
All I had to do
was pop it over,

34:15.734 --> 34:17.433
and now we just made it worse.

34:17.433 --> 34:19.667
So that sucks.

34:19.667 --> 34:21.333
- The wind's picking up.

34:21.333 --> 34:23.033
Everyone's tired.
Everyone's hungry.

34:23.033 --> 34:24.333
But I'm a problem solver.

34:24.333 --> 34:25.433
I'm not a panicker.

34:25.433 --> 34:27.200
If there's a situation,

34:27.200 --> 34:29.033
my mind is working
how to solve the problem.

34:29.033 --> 34:31.066
We just gotta keep
spinning that anchor.

34:31.066 --> 34:33.066
- Oh, sh--.

34:33.066 --> 34:34.066
- Hi, guys.
- Hi.

34:34.066 --> 34:35.734
- Hello.
- Update?

34:35.734 --> 34:37.300
- Yes.
So obviously we're having

34:37.300 --> 34:39.467
a few issues with
the anchor chain.

34:39.467 --> 34:42.066
So what I'm gonna do is,
I'm gonna get a tender

34:42.066 --> 34:45.100
to come in
and take you guys back to Split

34:45.100 --> 34:46.767
so then you can
enjoy your afternoon.

34:46.767 --> 34:48.367
- What happened
with the anchor chain?

34:48.367 --> 34:50.233
- I think we've been spinning
around a little bit.

34:50.233 --> 34:51.500
- It's really tangled, huh?
- Yeah.

34:51.500 --> 34:53.300
It's always really important,

34:53.300 --> 34:55.367
when there is something wrong
on a yacht,

34:55.367 --> 34:57.166
to let the guests know enough

34:57.166 --> 34:59.500
that they're comfortable
with the situation,

34:59.500 --> 35:02.100
but not to alarm them
or stress them out.

35:02.100 --> 35:03.500
Because the last thing
we want to do

35:03.500 --> 35:06.233
on their luxury holiday
is scare them.

35:06.233 --> 35:07.367
- Thank you.
- Pleasure.

35:07.367 --> 35:09.233
- All right.

35:09.233 --> 35:11.700
So go ahead and pull up
on the blue line,

35:11.700 --> 35:13.367
and then at the same time,

35:13.367 --> 35:15.233
you're loosening
on the port anchor.

35:15.233 --> 35:17.033
- Copy.

35:21.500 --> 35:23.000
- Awesome.

35:23.000 --> 35:24.233
[chains jingle]

35:24.233 --> 35:25.400
Stop there.
Stop there.

35:25.400 --> 35:27.066
That worked.

35:27.066 --> 35:28.400
Whatever line you have up there,

35:28.400 --> 35:30.266
I want you to tie
another line to it

35:30.266 --> 35:31.467
in the middle somewhere

35:31.467 --> 35:33.066
and attach it to the cleat.

35:33.066 --> 35:34.400
- Sorry, boss.

35:34.400 --> 35:36.333
Can you just go for that
again, please?

35:36.333 --> 35:38.400
- I think they're having
a problem up there.

35:38.400 --> 35:39.767
- Oh, I don't even know
what people were doing.

35:39.767 --> 35:41.533
Someone tells me
to move this line

35:41.533 --> 35:43.400
and attach that on there,
I'm like, "Yeah, okay."

35:43.400 --> 35:45.233
I do that,
and everyone with a brain

35:45.233 --> 35:47.000
was obviously
down in the tender.

35:47.000 --> 35:50.767
I'm just there for sheer
muscle power, you know?

35:50.767 --> 35:52.533
- So you're gonna pull up
on the blue line.

35:52.533 --> 35:54.400
[silverware clatters]
- How are they doing?

35:54.400 --> 35:57.333
- I've arranged a water taxi
to come pick them up.

35:57.333 --> 35:59.133
- Perfect.
- Well, in the meantime,

35:59.133 --> 36:00.533
they can enjoy these
lovely stuffed artichokes.

36:00.533 --> 36:02.333
- Yay!

36:02.333 --> 36:03.500
- We're going into
full distraction mode.

36:03.500 --> 36:05.133
- They're coming.

36:05.133 --> 36:07.133
- I'll put these here for you.

36:07.133 --> 36:08.500
- There's a lot at stake here
with our tip.

36:08.500 --> 36:10.166
We need to make sure
they're happy.

36:10.166 --> 36:12.433
- Sh--.

36:12.433 --> 36:14.033
- The lemon on top?
- Yeah, that's what makes it.

36:14.033 --> 36:15.433
- Makes it.
- Yeah?

36:15.433 --> 36:17.100
- This is like a real--
- Oh, that's good.

36:17.100 --> 36:18.367
- It's real.
- This is, like,

36:18.367 --> 36:20.133
plant-based paradise.
- Yeah.

36:20.133 --> 36:21.533
- [laughs]

36:21.533 --> 36:24.367
[engine revving]

36:24.367 --> 36:26.500
- Uh, just so you know,
the water taxi has arrived

36:26.500 --> 36:28.367
to take the guests
back to Split.

36:28.367 --> 36:30.100
We just need some help
with the luggage.

36:30.100 --> 36:32.033
- Okay, thank you.

36:32.033 --> 36:36.734
All crew, all crew.
Let's get into our whites.

36:36.734 --> 36:38.767
- I don't know if the
charter guests are pissed off because we haven't left yet.

36:38.767 --> 36:43.367
And now I see that they're
taking a tender back home.

36:43.367 --> 36:45.300
Is that gonna affect our tip?
I don't know.

36:45.300 --> 36:46.700
[engine rumbling]

36:46.700 --> 36:49.467
- And people think
yachting's easy.

36:49.467 --> 36:51.433
- Wes, Wes, Hannah.

36:51.433 --> 36:52.600
Just so you know,
all the luggage is loaded

36:52.600 --> 36:54.400
and in the tender.

36:54.400 --> 36:55.467
- Fantastic.
Thank you very much.

36:55.467 --> 36:57.333
- All crew, all crew.

36:57.333 --> 37:00.467
Can you come into the main salon
for guest departure?

37:00.467 --> 37:01.600
All crew, into the main salon.

37:01.600 --> 37:03.333
- Let's do this.

37:03.333 --> 37:05.133
- Right now,
we need to go to plan B.

37:05.133 --> 37:07.066
We've delayed the guests
long enough.

37:07.066 --> 37:09.133
Let's get 'em off the boat
so they can catch their flights.

37:12.600 --> 37:14.300
- Yeah.

37:14.300 --> 37:16.200
It's just so hard
because it's so tight.

37:16.200 --> 37:17.300
- Yeah.

37:17.300 --> 37:19.266
[woman laughs]
- No!

37:19.266 --> 37:21.133
- Guys, thank you so much.

37:21.133 --> 37:22.600
- Thank you so much.
- Sad to leave.

37:22.600 --> 37:24.433
- It was a pleasure
meeting you.

37:24.433 --> 37:26.300
- Awesome time.
[all chattering indistinctly]

37:26.300 --> 37:27.333
- Lovely to meet you.

37:27.333 --> 37:29.033
- [indistinct speech]

37:29.033 --> 37:30.567
- From the Mr. Skin team
out there,

37:30.567 --> 37:33.500
I just want you to know
we had a skintastic time.

37:33.500 --> 37:38.033
Not only was the service
five-star impeccable,

37:38.033 --> 37:40.100
but then you show up
with those shirts,

37:40.100 --> 37:41.500
which absolutely
blew our mind.

37:41.500 --> 37:43.233
- Hey, guys.

37:43.233 --> 37:47.300
[laughter and cheers]
- That's awesome.

37:47.300 --> 37:49.100
Chef Adam, you made it
delicious for everyone...

37:49.100 --> 37:50.633
- Thank you very much.
- And we appreciate that.

37:50.633 --> 37:52.500
- Appreciate that.
- And you guys down at the end,

37:52.500 --> 37:55.233
how you were able
to get the yacht

37:55.233 --> 37:57.567
so that we could be
so close to the caves

37:57.567 --> 37:59.567
was really above and beyond.

37:59.567 --> 38:02.633
Last but not least,
we call you Badass Captain,

38:02.633 --> 38:05.500
'cause we just--we're just
the biggest fans of you.

38:05.500 --> 38:08.433
And a small token of my
appreciation for the crew.

38:08.433 --> 38:10.100
Thank you so much
for everything.

38:10.100 --> 38:11.400
- We could not get you ashore.

38:11.400 --> 38:13.100
- I want you to know

38:13.100 --> 38:15.533
no one complained about that,
so all good.

38:15.533 --> 38:17.266
Bye, guys.
all: Bye!

38:17.266 --> 38:18.667
- Safe travels.

38:18.667 --> 38:20.533
- Mr. Skin's been
an absolute bundle of joy,

38:20.533 --> 38:22.233
but all us guys
are still thinking

38:22.233 --> 38:24.333
our tip went down
like a sh-- in the bath.

38:24.333 --> 38:27.266
[engine revving]

38:27.266 --> 38:28.533
- We'll deal with this later.

38:28.533 --> 38:30.400
In the meantime,
whoever needs to eat,

38:30.400 --> 38:32.533
grab a nibble,
and let's get back to it.

38:32.533 --> 38:39.533
♪ ♪

38:41.533 --> 38:43.066
- Go for it.

38:43.066 --> 38:44.100
I don't even care at this point.

38:44.100 --> 38:45.533
Just get us out of here.

38:45.533 --> 38:47.400
I feel like we're on our own
Gilligan's Island,

38:47.400 --> 38:51.233
except we're the island
that's floating around,

38:51.233 --> 38:52.700
and we can't go anywhere.

38:52.700 --> 38:54.500
- We don't have any guests on.
- Great idea.

38:54.500 --> 38:57.133
- I'm seeing the silver lining
here, guys.

38:57.133 --> 38:58.567
- Hi, troops.

38:58.567 --> 39:01.433
Oh, everyone's leaving me
at the lunch table.

39:01.433 --> 39:02.533
- I'll sit with you.
- Thanks, Bobby.

39:02.533 --> 39:03.700
That's very kind.

39:05.567 --> 39:08.433
Do you know?
- It's a full-on rat's nest

39:08.433 --> 39:11.033
of chain on the anchor.
- How did that happen?

39:11.033 --> 39:13.300
Like, you drug too much chain
into too shallow area.

39:13.300 --> 39:15.133
- Yeah, right.
It just--

39:15.133 --> 39:17.266
we spun around in circles
all night.

39:17.266 --> 39:19.166
Pulling the anchors probably
together, however--

39:19.166 --> 39:21.300
you know, whichever,
however it ended up.

39:21.300 --> 39:23.633
It's just a mess.
[scoffs]

39:24.700 --> 39:27.133
- How do we get the pressure
off of them?

39:27.133 --> 39:28.266
- Oh, okay, I see.

39:28.266 --> 39:30.166
So you want me to undo this.

39:30.166 --> 39:31.433
[grunts]

39:31.433 --> 39:32.567
- You ready?

39:32.567 --> 39:34.400
- Go, go, go.
- Go.

39:34.400 --> 39:37.600
[chains clinking]

39:37.600 --> 39:40.200
- Sh--. Hold it.
both: Stop!

39:40.200 --> 39:41.600
- They may have to cut
the anchor chain,

39:41.600 --> 39:43.700
and now that's weeks
without a job.

39:43.700 --> 39:45.166
Sh--.

39:52.600 --> 39:53.033
[chains clinking]

39:54.467 --> 39:56.333
- Sh--. Stop!
- Stop!

39:56.333 --> 39:58.433
- Hi, Mom.

39:58.433 --> 40:04.667
I really want to come home.

40:04.667 --> 40:06.600
No, I know.

40:06.600 --> 40:09.300
I know it's the best thing
for me to stay.

40:09.300 --> 40:11.533
I really want to make it
to my gran's funeral.

40:11.533 --> 40:13.600
I just really want to be there
for my mom.

40:13.600 --> 40:15.500
If you want me to come,
I will come.

40:15.500 --> 40:18.100
But my gran raised me
to never be a quitter.

40:18.100 --> 40:21.367
And I know that she would have
wanted me to have been here.

40:21.367 --> 40:23.500
I love you, Mom.
I'll chat you later.

40:23.500 --> 40:25.500
Okay, bye.

40:25.500 --> 40:29.100
♪ ♪

40:29.100 --> 40:30.367
Do you have
any more rubbish in here?

40:30.367 --> 40:32.066
- No, I got it all out.

40:32.066 --> 40:34.100
There's a pair of panties
over there, though,

40:34.100 --> 40:35.700
if you want to toss those
in the rubbish.

40:35.700 --> 40:38.367
- Oh, yeah, I've got
the rubbish bin here.

40:38.367 --> 40:40.633
- Hey, I just want to say
I'm really sorry.

40:40.633 --> 40:43.066
I know I'm, like, keeping down
the whole crew.

40:43.066 --> 40:44.500
I'm trying my best.

40:44.500 --> 40:46.500
And I know you're
going through a lot,

40:46.500 --> 40:49.100
and I'm being kind of selfish
with all this.

40:49.100 --> 40:51.500
You really can't compare
my situation

40:51.500 --> 40:53.433
with what Bugs
is going through.

40:53.433 --> 40:55.166
I need to pull it together
and move forward.

40:55.166 --> 40:57.066
I'm trying my best
to keep it to myself,

40:57.066 --> 40:59.600
but I am apparently
not doing a good job at it.

40:59.600 --> 41:01.533
So I just wanted to say
I'm sorry.

41:01.533 --> 41:04.667
I'm here for you, and I
appreciate you being here.

41:04.667 --> 41:07.233
- I'm not even sure
what she's apologizing for.

41:07.233 --> 41:09.734
Okay.

41:09.734 --> 41:11.667
- Is that all the way up?

41:11.667 --> 41:13.400
- Yeah, we're--
we're holding there, Max.

41:13.400 --> 41:15.667
- No way.

41:15.667 --> 41:17.000
- Sh--.

41:17.000 --> 41:18.066
- Now we've got our line stuck

41:18.066 --> 41:19.367
in between the knots too,

41:19.367 --> 41:20.734
making the knot even worse.

41:20.734 --> 41:22.533
Yeah, it's really twisted.
Yeah.

41:22.533 --> 41:24.000
And it goes underneath.

41:24.000 --> 41:26.400
- What we're doing
isn't working.

41:26.400 --> 41:28.367
- Sh--.
- Can you use that pry bar?

41:28.367 --> 41:29.400
[chain jingles]

41:29.400 --> 41:31.000
This is a nightmare.

41:31.000 --> 41:34.367
- That chick wanted to do
a handstand off of here.

41:34.367 --> 41:35.767
Can we jump in, Captain?

41:35.767 --> 41:37.467
- I don't care if you jump
in the water.

41:37.467 --> 41:40.033
- Really?
- I wish I could jump in.

41:40.033 --> 41:41.767
- I'm getting out of here.

41:41.767 --> 41:43.033
- What's it look like, Bobby?

41:43.033 --> 41:44.700
- We're getting there.

41:44.700 --> 41:47.033
- Girls, you want to
go for a swim?

41:47.033 --> 41:49.233
- I'm coming.
- Hell, yeah.

41:49.233 --> 41:54.166
♪ ♪

41:54.166 --> 41:56.567
- Don't lose that top now, yeah?

41:56.567 --> 41:58.133
- Oh, yeah.
- It's not bad.

41:58.133 --> 41:59.667
Just make sure you pin drop,
yeah?

41:59.667 --> 42:01.166
- It doesn't take the whole crew

42:01.166 --> 42:02.433
to figure out this anchor mess,

42:02.433 --> 42:03.667
so while we're stranded,

42:03.667 --> 42:05.166
we might as well have some fun.

42:05.166 --> 42:07.700
- Three, two, one!

42:07.700 --> 42:11.433
[both scream]

42:11.433 --> 42:12.767
- [gasps]
- Whoo!

42:12.767 --> 42:14.767
- Whoo!
- Sh--!

42:14.767 --> 42:19.433
♪ ♪

42:19.433 --> 42:20.700
- There you go.

42:20.700 --> 42:22.200
Good God, Malia's hot.

42:22.200 --> 42:23.467
[laughs]
Holy sh--.

42:23.467 --> 42:25.433
Oh, you.
I forgot about you.

42:25.433 --> 42:27.433
Butts are out.
Simple as that.

42:29.000 --> 42:30.200
- It's getting there.
- This last bit

42:30.200 --> 42:31.467
I don't think's gonna come, bro.

42:31.467 --> 42:32.600
[speaks indistinctly]

42:32.600 --> 42:34.200
[chain clinks, water splashes]

42:34.200 --> 42:35.467
Just chip away at it.

42:35.467 --> 42:38.200
- I like seeing that.

42:38.200 --> 42:39.200
- [grunts]

42:39.200 --> 42:42.033
Oh, this is so tight.

42:42.033 --> 42:44.200
- It's illegal to pull
into a port without anchors.

42:44.200 --> 42:46.734
If we have to cut the anchors,
it's gonna kill our season.

42:46.734 --> 42:48.533
I'm not leaving
the frickin' anchors.

42:48.533 --> 42:51.033
It's not happening.
- Oh, man.

42:51.033 --> 42:52.200
Come on, this time.

42:52.200 --> 42:53.600
[chains clinking]

42:53.600 --> 42:56.033
- Huh?
- F---. Holy sh--.

42:57.567 --> 43:00.000
[dramatic musical flourish]

43:01.600 --> 43:05.767
- For more on "Below Deck Med,"
go to bravotv.com.
